#- §l§nPreface:§0
§0This book was made possible by the very amazing contributions from the co-authors. All have contributed to this book and without them it would be impossible to make. The time they put in to perfect the different brews  is amazing!
#- §l§nBrewing:§0
§0As instructions on how to set up a brewery can be found on the wiki, I will not delve much into that, though I will state the basics. To make a brewery you will either need a large barrel or a small barrel. A barrel of each wood type is 
#- required as some brews require a special kind of wood to age properly. §0
§0Aging drinks is easy, but do not age distillates and do note distill aged alcohol as they will ruin the alcohol and turn them into crud. some types of alcohols (that are able to 
#- be aged) can be done by throwing them into a barrel. You can place them in a barrle for a long amount of time and they will keep raising in years. The more a bottle of alcohol is aged, the more expensive it will be. Distilled alcohols can only be 
#- distilled to some degree, after a few distillations they will stop being further pure/distilled as they would probably be 100% alcohol. Without further ado, let's get right into the recipes!
#- §l§nOurTrueLeader's Liquid Cocaine:§0
§0> 40 sugar cane§0
§0> 8 long grass§0
§0> 6 cactus§0
§0> 8 redstone dust§0
§0===================Cook: 15 minutes§0
§0Distill: 4+ times.§0
§0Age: Do not age.§0
§0Barrel Type: N/A
#- §l§nEpic Stout:§0
§0> 24 wheat§0
§0===================Cook: 15 minutes§0
§0Distill: Do not distill.§0
§0Age: 4 years§0
§0Barrel Type: Dark Oak§0
§0

